  "body": "<!-- Please use this template while reporting a bug and provide as much info as possible. Not doing so may result in your bug not being addressed in a timely manner. Thanks!\r\n\r\nIf the matter is security related, please disclose it privately via https://kubernetes.io/security/\r\n-->\r\n\r\n\r\n**What happened**:\r\n\r\nDuring I develop a driver that supports raw block devices but do not need to be attached to nodes, I found it would fail when a pod mount a raw block device.\r\n\r\nPS: I use cluster-driver register and make requiredAttach as false.\r\n\r\nkubectl get csidriver csi-xxx -o yaml\r\n```\r\napiVersion: storage.k8s.io/v1beta1\r\nkind: CSIDriver\r\nmetadata:\r\n  creationTimestamp: \"2019-06-27T07:20:22Z\"\r\n  name: csi-xxx\r\n  resourceVersion: \"5029920\"\r\n  selfLink: /apis/storage.k8s.io/v1beta1/csidrivers/csi-lvmplugin\r\n  uid: b31c24ea-9872-40ed-b917-0b8d6d1124e5\r\nspec:\r\n  attachRequired: false\r\n  podInfoOnMount: false\r\n```\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/12230714/60805861-00bbbe80-a1b4-11e9-8ecd-d8ff680491a2.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n**What you expected to happen**:\r\n\r\nMount a raw block device successfully.\r\n\r\n**How to reproduce it (as minimally and precisely as possible)**:\r\n\r\n1. a driver that supports raw block devices but do not need to be attached to nodes, I found it would fail when a pod mount a raw block device.\r\n2. use cluster-driver register and make requiredAttach as false.\r\n3. create a pod with raw block devices\r\n\r\n**Anything else we need to know?**:\r\n\r\n**Environment**:\r\n- Kubernetes version (use `kubectl version`): 1.15\r\n- Cloud provider or hardware configuration: BaiduCloud\r\n- OS (e.g: `cat /etc/os-release`):\r\n- Kernel (e.g. `uname -a`):\r\n- Install tools:\r\n- Network plugin and version (if this is a network-related bug):\r\n- Others:\r\n",
